--------------------
Installing musl-libc
--------------------

The musl-libc library libc, libm and libpthread for applications, and therefore
needs to be compiled for all architectures in the system.

NOTE: do a "make distclean" in-between building for individual architectures

1. Build & install musl-libc for aarch64:

  $ ./configure --prefix=/usr/local/popcorn/aarch64 --target=aarch64-linux-gnu --enable-debug --enable-gcc-wrapper --enable-optimize --disable-shared CC=aarch64-linux-gnu-gcc CFLAGS='-ffunction-sections -fdata-sections'
  $ make install

2. Build & install musl-libc for x86_64:

  $ make distclean
  $ ./configure --prefix=/usr/local/popcorn/x86_64 --target=x86_64-linux-gnu --enable-debug --enable-gcc-wrapper --enable-optimize --disable-shared CFLAGS='-ffunction-sections -fdata-sections -fasynchronous-unwind-tables'
  $ make install

3. You can speed the build up by enabling parallel jobs:

  $ make -j<# of parallel jobs>

